import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['group'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['group'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['group'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['group'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['group'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['group'] = pd.to_numeric(data['group'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['group'])]
    avg_group_size = data['group'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axhline(avg_group_size, color='red', label=f'Average Group Size: {avg_group_size:.2f}')
    ax.bar(['Average Group Size'], [avg_group_size], color='blue')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average group size?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['person'], bins=10, color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Number of people per group')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['person'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['person'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people per group?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['group_size'] = data.groupby('group')['person'].transform('count')
    group_sizes = data['group_size'].value_counts().sort_index()
    ax = group_sizes.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    ax.set_xlabel('Group Size')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.axvline(x=group_sizes.idxmax(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Most Common Group Size: {group_sizes.idxmax():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the most common group size?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="group", y="person", data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel("Group")
    ax.set_ylabel("Number of People")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of people across groups?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
